<time>1551602397389</time>< rating>

<review>Had a dental clean appointment, where Dr Cornehl recommended I get 4 fillings, fair enough. A couple weeks later, receive a difficult to understand insurance cost estimate, before my appointment -- I look through it carefully, determine that my copayment for the fillings will be ~$250.

I arrive at my appointment, and am told that my copayment is actually ~$1,000! Of course, these misunderstandings with insurance do happen, but after I decide not to go ahead with the appointment (wanting to do a little more cost comparison before I elect for this large bill), Dr Cornehl has the nerve to lecture me on the importance of planning ahead for such things. I'm sorry, if a patient who carefully reads a bill can't understand it because it is full of technical jargon and chooses to walk away for a $1000+ bill, is that the patient's fault? Staff is always friendly and attentive!< /text>
<user_id>118124621107606121369<//user_id>< Resp>

<Review>I visited Northridge Dentalworks yesterday for a consultation, dental exam, and x-rays.  I was experiencing pain and inflammation in my upper right molar as a result of a poorly done root canal performed by a former dentist about 14 months ago in Woodland Hills.  After having horrible experiences with the last two dentists that I‚Äôve had the displeasure of being a patient of, I was losing faith in finding an honest and caring dentist who isn‚Äôt just focused on upselling unnecessary procedures or overcharging/taking advantage of patients. I WISH I HAD FOUND DR. TAVAKOL AND HER AMAZING STAFF SOONER!

I needed an appointment as soon as possible and was accommodated to be seen for a same day appointment with ease.  There was ample, convenient and free visitor parking available when I arrived. The front office staff was courteous, efficient, and professional. Rocio assisted me with any questions and concerns that I had with a genuinely caring, patient, and professional demeanor.  The waiting room and back offices were very clean and comfortable.

The wait time was reasonable and I was called to the back room for x-rays.  After x-rays were completed, I was promptly taken to another room to be examined by the doctor.  A dental assistant named Patty made sure that I was comfortable and offered me a neck pillow.  Upon being greeted by Dr. Tavakol and explaining the reason for my visit, I knew that I was in good hands as energy speaks louder than words.  She was very attentive, kind and personable. During my exam, Dr. Tavakol was gentle and throughly went over my x-rays with me in detail.  She didn‚Äôt become bothered, condescending or frustrated  when I had multiple questions as my last two dentists had.  Her bedside manner is excellent and she put me at ease!  Apparently, my former dentist performed a root canal on my upper right molar (tooth #1) which was completely unnecessary. <review>Very few employees in the store, they are ringing up everyone at the customer service line. The manager was unwilling to accommodate me on the buy 1 get 2 free deal for the Animal crossing amiibo cards. There were only two left. I had been there before the last time this sale happened and the cards hadn't rung up properly and he begrudgingly fixed it for me when I explained that the sale is supposed to include the cards. So here I was, this time the sale was taking the cards properly but sadly there were only 2 card packs left, I was getting some figurines too so I requested the ability to apply a 3 pack amiibo figurine set as the "buy one" so the last two card packs would be mine. he refused... fair enough... the sale did only specify "All Animal crossing amiibo" 7.99 and under... the 3 pack set was 24.99, again, not trying to get that discounted... I simply wanted him to make an exception because there were not enough card packs to apply themselves to the sale. So I asked if he could let me get the card packs as a buy one get one instead, since there was no second one. (this would not change the sale price at all if there had been three card packs) otherwise, since there were only two I would have to pay full price for both... he refused to budge even for this so I walked out with only the three individual figurines. This manager lost out on my 37 dollar potential purchase and I ended up only paying the 7.99 for the three figures. I won't be going back to this particular location anymore. plenty of other stores out there who will price match me. Shame on this location's manager :(< /review>< date>
1500365897634<//date>

<time>1470165099645</time><rating>4< /rating>< text>
I was looking for a jumbo teddy bear for my grandson's first birthday. Called the store and they were super helpful over the phone, describing all the bears that they had.

Went in the next day and found exactly what I'd hoped for, as well as a nice selection of FAO Schwarz toys. Again, the sales people were very helpful.

The bear and I then had an organic lunch at Sharkeys just down from Toys "R" Us.

The store is located in the Janss mall, very close to the 101 and Moorpark Road. It looks like a regular shopping center on the outside but the inner section has a cute little play yard for kids, as well as a number of coin-operated rides and a fountain area to play in.< /text>

<GmapID>0x80d94515b50c44f7:0x912e09d3bfecc401< /GmapID><Text>I don‚Äôt write many reviews, reserving them for exceptionally good, or bad, encounters. However, my recent experience with Andre Enriques while obtaining a mortgage definitely warrants an excellent one.

The search for a lender started with combing through Yelp reviews, looking for mortgage bankers with excellent reviews and experience with VA loans. After narrowing the field to five lenders, I compared their advertised rates on the internet. This resulted in two candidates.

These firms were asked to provide quotes in a loan estimate format.  Neither were happy about giving me this information before I committed to obtaining my loan from them, but did provide it. Andre gave it to me after reassurance that his numbers would not be revealed to another lender. It took three requests from his competition to produce what I asked for, and when I compared their numbers, it became evident why.

The seller had given $10,000 to cover my closing costs. Both lenders would have left me with no out-of-pocket outlays for the loan, but Andre‚Äôs numbers left approximately $6,000 that could be used to buy down the interest rate. The competition had eaten up the excess with inflated fees and extra charges.

Andre‚Äôs service throughout the process was amazing. The man must eat and sleep with his phone on and a laptop next to him. I don‚Äôt recall even one time he didn‚Äôt answer the phone, or call me back within a few minutes. Emails were answered almost immediately, no matter what time I sent them. He guided me through every step of the process, from providing a list of documents that I would need to submit, to informing me the loan had funded.

This theater was clean from outside all the way to inside the theater. Staff was great and helpful. One thing that online said is that there is valet parking but the box office said there is not. Signs on mission lead to parking lots that either aren't there or a couple of very long blocks away. There's a parking garage but the box office said next door but there isn't one next door. Street parking is 2 hours or less so that eliminates movie goers. The theater is great otherwise though. We would love to go back but the parking is an issue. <text>Well, you saw me again soon.  You still have that dreadful reserved seat setup -- this in a house of theaters that never sell out. <Rate>2< /Rate>< Review>
Our most recent visit was during opening weekend of the biggest movie in history, by box office earnings, but it was obvious that the theater was understaffed and/or poorly managed.

The concessions stand routinely has very long wait times for basic popcorn and drink orders. It was especially bad during this big weekend, when one would expect extra staff and a streamlined process for filling orders.

There were several problem patrons in the theater who made it impossible to enjoy the film, and when I went to find a manager, he just wanted to know if someone was drunk--as if that were the threshold of a disturbance worthy of acting on a complaint. We considered leaving and demanding a refund, but simply telling one of the obnoxious groups that management was coming made them leave first.

I was vaguely aware about an hour later that he had eventually made his way into our theater to look around.

The bathroom reeked of urine and was strewn with trash.

Two stars because we think the seats are pretty comfortable with enough room that the person next to me texting through the entire movie was something that I was eventually able to block out of my consciousness.</Review>

<text>Staffing is incredibly polite, courteous, and attentive to you as the customer.  The physical facility could use a remodel to clean up the toilets and the actual theaters.

After viewing several movies each theater's seating is dramatically different.  The seats are either good or uncomfortably bad.  Moving to a different row does not help and we would feel guilty utilizing plush vacant seats next to the handicap designations.

The restrooms are tagged and carved throughout from the local juveniles.  If you can look beyond the markings the bathroom is acceptable.
